name: WhiteSpace
description:
WhiteSpace SD Model


It's called Whitespace, but it's not really whitespace at all. I was trying to add a more colorful and mysterious feel to the Pastelmix line of models.

Some prompts that work well with the models include the following.

"prism, glowing, glitter, particles, bloom, extra lights, cinematic lights, glowing white particles, +a"


There are three types of models (WhiteSpace Prism, Quasar, and Black), each with slightly different characteristics.

First of all, the Prism model is the base model for the other models and has the most stylish and distinctive look. It has a jewel-like design and unusual light effects. Recommended setting #1 is the best fit.

The Quasar model takes the Prism and mixes it with the Chilloutmix and Ultracolor models to create an unusual semi-photorealistic model. It's still an unusual color, but it's a bit more like the other semi-photorealistic models. This model can be a bit unstable. Recommended setting #2 works best.

The Black model was created by mixing Prism with a little bit of Helltaker lora, Maplestory lora, and World Flipper lora to create a bold and strong style. Enjoy the cartoon-like feel with strong lines and contrast. Recommended setting #2 works best.

A detailed comparison of each model is shown in the image below.
(WSB = Black, WSQ = Quasar, WSP = Prism)



Based on the stable diffusion WebUI, the recommended settings are:

Recommended setting #1 (oldQPrompt):

- Prompt: masterpiece, best quility, high_quality, high_resolution, masterpiece*portait,

- Negative prompt: lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, text, error, missing fingers, extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry, artist name, ugly, duplicate, morbid, mutilated, tranny, trans, transsexual, hermaphrodite, extra fingers, mutated hands, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn face, mutation, deformed, ugly, blurry, bad anatomy, bad proportions, extra limbs, cloned face, disfigured. more than 2 nipples. ugly, extra limbs, bad anatomy, gross proportions, malformed limbs, missing arms, missing legs, extra arms, extra legs, mutated hands, fused fingers, too many fingers, long neck

- Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras or DPM++ SDE Karras

- Upscaler (optional): 4x-UltraSharp

- CFG Scale : 6~7

-Sampling steps: 20

Recommended setting #2 (newQPrompt):

- Prompt: (finely detailed, distinct image, ultra resolution, extremely amazing detailed, awesome detailed), subsurface scattering, best ratio four finger and one thumb, masterpiece, best quility, high_quality,

- Negative prompts: lowers, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), EasyNegative, text,error, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, artist name

- Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras or DPM++ SDE Karras (Black model shows good quality even with Euler a)

- Upscaler (optional): 4x-UltraSharp

- CFG Scale : 6~7

-Sampling steps: 20~26

These are the settings in my case and I don't see any problems not following them, but in my case the above settings have the highest quality.

modelVersions.name: WhiteSpace Prism
modelVersions.description:
W H I T E S P A C E P R I S M

V1 0.1.0 Changelogs

- First Version!

- The following models were used for the merge:

pastelmix x 0.25 + anything-v4.5 x 0.5 + Counterfeit-V2.5 x 0.25 = WS1

WS1 x 0.5 + qwerty_v2 x 0.5 = WS2

WS2 x 0.25 + HyperBombMix-fp16-no-ema x 0.5 + schoolAnime_schoolAnime x 0.25 = WS3

WS3 x 0.25 + colormixed x 0.5 + nullV22_nullV22 x 0.25 = WS4(=WhiteSpace Prism V1, WSP)

- This version includes the following files:
WS4.safetensors(also .ckpt) : Full checkpoint file of This model
WS4_Pruned.safetensors(also .ckpt) : no-ema + fp16
